Interface Stack<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - Type of data stored for this entry
    All Superinterfaces:
    Collection
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LinkedStack

    public interface Stack<E>
extends Collection
    A collection of objects that are inserted and removed according to the last-in first-out principle. Although similar in purpose, this interface differs from java.util.Stack.
    Author:
    Michael T. Goodrich, Roberto Tamassia, Michael H. Goldwasser, Maria Jump
